h time I come away feeling like I never truly mastered it despite having \"learned\" the syntax, even if I have done deep depth into Angular internals (pre-AI era). Now, I have a personal situation where I am in Angular training program (in an institutional context with rules and consequences) again, and I am unsure if they're teaching legacy Angular (but when in Rome, do as Rome do). So. First question: @NgModule - declarations vs imports vs exports vs providers, what are those? I still don't understand even after reading multiple blog post explanations. (I do know modern JS import syntax)","models":["GLM-5-Turbo"]},"fff7a2dc-0adc-4d16-8954-92fe21bb6ee2":{"id":"fff7a2dc-0adc-4d16-8954-92fe21bb6ee2","parentId":"1b24b99f-a88b-433a-9230-929e92fbf04b","childrenIds":["4c01e72b-dda3-4f3e-9240-892ca022e61d"],"role":"user","timestamp":1777432166}},"currentId":"327f677b-2615-47f3-9805-56c10b13538f"},"tags":[],"features":[{"type":"tool_selector","server":"tool_selector_h","status":"hidden"}],"enable_thinking":true,"timestamp":1777426069412,"extra":{}},"updated_at":1777434106,"created_at":1777426069,"share_id":null,"archived":false,"pinned":false,"meta":{"auto_web_search":false,"flags":null,"mcp_servers":[],"models":["GLM-5-Turbo"],"workspace_id":"9e049062-2b54-41cd-b09f-ca85f744e378"},"folder_id":null,"message_version":1,"type":"default","im_context":null}